FAQs
What are the admission requirements for medical schools in Malaysia?

Admission requirements typically include a high school diploma with strong grades in science subjects, proficiency in English, and passing an entrance exam or interview.

Is a medical degree from Malaysia recognized internationally?

Yes, degrees from accredited Malaysian medical schools are recognized internationally. Graduates can sit for international licensing exams to practice medicine in various countries.

What is the average cost of study medicine in Malaysia?

The cost of studying medicine in Malaysia varies by institution, but tuition fees range from $10,000 to $25,000 per year. The cost of living is also affordable, averaging around $5,000 to $7,000 per year.

Can international students work while studying in Malaysia?

International students are allowed to work part-time for up to 20 hours per week during semester breaks. However, they must obtain permission from their university and comply with Malaysian immigration regulations.

What support services are available for international students in Malaysia?

Malaysian universities offer a range of support services, including orientation programs, academic advising, language support, and assistance with visa applications and accommodation.
